children.subject: me too, and yet a bunch of my friends got in the class even though our spots on the wait list were close-ish

history.content:
Have you checked if there are enrollment restrictions for the class? Sometimes they reserve a certain number of seats for students with certain profiles (specific majors, specific years, transfer students, etc) so even though there are open seats in the class, you may not meet the requirements for the seats that are open. 

Another thing that could keep you from getting in is if you have a course conflict. You won't be placed in the class if you have a course conflict so you will need to fill out the CS course conflict form.

They could be holding seats until they hire more staff but it's a bit late for that so I would guess this probably isn't what is happening.

The waitlist gets processed at certain times of the day, it's possible everything is working properly and you will get put in when the waitlist is processed (if you waited 24 hours though then this isn't what is happening).

It may also be something else more specific to this situation but those things listed above are some common things.
